All Implemented Interfaces:
Accessible, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Scrollable, Serializable
public class CatalogTree
extends JTree

This class manages the display of Content within a Tree control. Content is provide by one or more NodeManagers. A standard set of NodeManagers is initially added when the tree is instantiated. Developers can add further NodeManagers if desired.

Constructor Detail

CatalogTree

public CatalogTree()
constructs with predefined tree model, mouse listeners, look-and-feel, and adds the standard NodeManagers and MouseHandlers. By default, drag-and-drop is not enabled.

See Also:
enableDragAndDrop()
Method Detail

enableDragAndDrop

public void enableDragAndDrop()
invoke this method to cause the CatalogTree to become a DragSource. Once invoked, you cannot undo the effect.

getSelectionData

public Content[] getSelectionData()
obtain the underlying content of the currently selected nodes

Returns:
an array of Content corresponding with selected tree nodes, an empty array is returned if nothing is currently selected

setShowWaitingCursor

public void setShowWaitingCursor(boolean show)
Sets whether a waiting cursor should be shown when the tree is expanding. The default value is true (showing waiting cursor.)

Parameters:
show - true == show waiting cursor; false == do not show waiting cursor.
